This paper analyzes the security implications of third-party resources loading on the web, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study focuses on the web and its interconnected services, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under web technologies (cs.WEB). The paper also discusses the trust relationship between first-party and third-party resources, which could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI). The study involves large-scale data analysis, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
